I'd like to fadeToggle everything in the div "container" but not links and not the div with the class "to_top". But with the following code everything in the div "container" fadetoggles. Where I'm wrong?

Thanks.

    $('#container').not(".to_top","a").on('tap', function(e) {  
        $("#headline").fadeToggle(700);
        $("#headline_tap").fadeToggle();
    });

I'd like to fadeToggle everything in the div "container" but not links and not the div with the class "to_top". But with the following code everything in the div "container" fadetoggles. Where I'm wrong?

Thanks.

    if (!$("#container").hasClass("to_top")) {
        $('#container').on('tap', function(e) {
